race.comment: KRAKARIB (3) wasn't beaten too far at Gatton first-up and then led at Ballina when missing narrowly. He still has plenty up his sleeve and is likely to skip across and take plenty of running down. BEAU WITNESS (2) has been racing in stronger since his comfortable win here this grade. Maps well and is suited with the 2kg claim. Is up to this and is a player. GALWAY HUSSLER (4) resumes and has placed 3/4 fresh. Has strong form at the track and missed a lip in a recent Gatton trial. Has a 2kg claim and a bold return is on the cards. CARRIBEAN KING (6) has had two starts since the switch to the Currie yard and did nothing as a $2.3F here last time. Gets some gear tweaks and he has the ability. Needs to be kept safe.
